    </correction>
    <normalization default="yes" method="tags">
     <p>Modern editorial line division, spacing, punctuation, and
     capitalisation have been silently imposed on the base text.
     Paleographic information about the base witness (damage,
     hard-to-read letter forms letters, etc.) has been silently
     suppressed.  These features can be recovered from the apparatus
     (which preserves paleographic encoding about the readings in each
     witness) and from the relevant sgml files containing witness
     transcriptions.</p> 
    </normalization>
    <segmentation>
     <p>Edition has been segmented according to modern editorial
     convention (i.e. line boundaries mark modern editorial line
     boundaries; caesura elements mark modern editorial
     caesurae).</p>
